(Resilience Lab Command and Tool Reference) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This page covers every Docker Compose command and probe tool used in Lecture 08 resilience work) Tj
T*
(\(web + api + redis\).) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Docker Compose Commands) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose up --build) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Build images and start services in foreground mode.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Reproduces startup timing and failure windows while logs stream directly.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose up --build) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose up -d --build) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Build and start services in detached mode.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Fast way to boot the full stack and keep terminal free for probes/logs.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose up -d --build) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose up -d redis) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Start only Redis service.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Isolate dependency startup behavior before starting api/web.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose up -d redis) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose up -d) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Start services using existing images.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Quick restart when code/images are already built.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose up -d) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose ps) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Show container status and health state.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: First checkpoint to see starting, healthy, or unhealthy before deep debugging.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose ps) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose logs -f web api redis) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Follow live logs for all core services.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Correlate probe failures with exact restart/connect timing.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose logs -f web api redis) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(docker compose logs -f api) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Follow one service?s logs.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Narrow focus when api readiness is suspicious.) Tj
T*
(- Example:) Tj
T*
(    docker compose logs -f api) Tj
ET
endstream
endobj
