/F1 10 Tf
14 TL
54 738 Td
(    curl http://localhost:3001) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3000/readyz   # include HTTP status headers) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(wget) Tj
T*
(- What it is: CLI downloader that can also perform HTTP probes.) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Lightweight machine probes in containers and health checks.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Common in minimal images; simple non-interactive readiness test.) Tj
T*
(- Examples:) Tj
T*
(    wget -qO- http://localhost:3000/readyz) Tj
T*
(    wget -qO- http://api:3000/readyz) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Redis CLI Commands Used in Lab) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(PING) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Basic liveness check to Redis.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Fastest signal that Redis is reachable.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(SET <key> <value> / GET <key>) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Store and retrieve known values.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Confirms reads/writes work, not just socket connectivity.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(INCR <key>) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: Increment counter atomically.) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Matches this lab?s visits pattern used by api.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(KEYS *) Tj
T*
(- What it is for: List keys \(small/dev datasets only\).) Tj
T*
(- Why use it: Quick visibility while learning/debugging.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Examples:) Tj
T*
(    PING) Tj
T*
(    SET course cs426) Tj
T*
(    GET course) Tj
T*
(    INCR visits) Tj
T*
(    GET visits) Tj
T*
(    KEYS *) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Recommended Command Sequence During Incidents) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(    docker compose ps) Tj
T*
(    docker compose logs -f web api redis) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3000/healthz) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3000/readyz) Tj
T*
(    curl -i http://localhost:3001) Tj
T*
(    docker compose exec api sh) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This order prevents random debugging and gives fast triage: container state -> logs -> probes) Tj
T*
(-> in-container verification.) Tj
ET
endstream
